<div class="story">
<p>Pine Island is an ocean front subdivision in the southern most area of Corolla just past the <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/" title="Duck">Duck</a> town line. Pine Island has an active home owners association which takes care of the private roads, the 2 tennis courts, the 2 community pools and the numerous beach accesses. There is a private airstrip for Pine Island owners but no facilities for storage, so it is drop off only. The tract of land opposite Pine Island belongs to the Audubon Society and is a bird sanctuary, so the sounds views will never be built over. </p>
